our code. It's that we don't store our tests so they can be rerun automatically. And this,

00:15:00.580 --> 00:15:05.219
to me, is just like the essence of Hadley. I mean, this is exactly why I love Hadley.

00:15:05.219 --> 00:15:09.440
Because he starts it off by saying, you know, it's not that we don't test our code. So,

00:15:09.440 --> 00:15:16.440
it's not that we're like terrible people. It's just we have room for improvement.

